items.title: ‘Cranky’ Opossum Lands in Hospital After Eating Costco Bakery Item
items.content:
A “cranky” but curious opossum found itself in the hospital after indulging in a popular Costco dessert, Nebraska Wildlife Rehab reported on Instagram.

Real estate agent Kim Doggett left a Costco chocolate mousse cake sitting on her back patio after running out of fridge space. “I always have a house full and we cook a lot,” Doggett told Forbes, “and when you run out of room in the fridge you just sit it on the table outside in the winter.” It was her son who found the “choc-oholic” critter munching the cake. When he went out to drop some peanut butter balls which needed to firm up, he found a mostly eaten cake and chocolate footprints leading to an animal that “just didn’t look right.”

“We googled chocolate with possums because I know with dogs it’s poisonous and thought this would not be good for this little girl,” Doggett explained.

Related: Costco Members Share Wildest Items They’ve Seen Customers Return

Nebraska Wildlife Rehab eventually took control of the opossum and gave it a full medical exam which revealed the chocolate may have been the least of its worries. Her bloodwork found she was suffering from lead toxicity, which is unfortunately “a common issue” for wildlife. “This is a common issue in wildlife, with different causes for different species, and it will take several weeks of treatment and supportive care to chelate the lead from her body,” the center’s executive director, Laura Stastny, told Forbes.

The marsupial was given activated charcoal and lots of fluids, and will be released back into the wild once she’s made a full recovery. While the center’s doctors noted that she had made it through a little more than half of the cake, rather than the whole thing, the opossum was “a little cranky about our ‘zero chocolate’ policy.”

Doggett is hoping to see the opossum back in her neighborhood once it’s out of the hospital, and already knows what she won’t be serving at its coming-home party. “Definitely not chocolate!” the realtor pledged.
